parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the backup camera can cause the driver to lose visibility when reversing, increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The backup camera screen goes black
is distorted
or is intermittently unavailable.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake light switch can prevent the vehicle from starting, leaving the driver stranded and potentially in dangerous situations.
symptoms: The vehicle will not start with the push-button start
and the brake light switch fails intermittently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission problems can cause the vehicle to hesitate or fail to move, increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The transmission shudders
the vehicle hesitates to move
or the vehicle will not shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corrosion of the battery cables can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to unexpected stalls or failures.
symptoms: The battery needs to be replaced frequently due to corrosion of the battery cables.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the FEB system can cause the vehicle to fail to brake or respond to emergency situations, increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The FEB system warning light illuminates
the system becomes unavailable
or the system gives false warnings.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Gear shift problems can cause the vehicle to hesitate or fail to move, increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The gear shift will not leave park when the car is first started
usually when the vehicle is cold.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the airbag system can lead to serious injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Airbag light stays on or flickers
occupant sensor not working
airbag system failure warning
weight sensors and seatbelt sensors fail to activate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the brake system can lead to accidents or loss of control of the vehicle.
symptoms: Brake pedal feels hard or stuck
brake lights do not turn on
brake pedal switch failure
brake light switch went out
brake pedal has to be pumped to release.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the front radar sensor can lead to false alerts, unnecessary braking, or failure of the automatic emergency braking system, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Front radar sensor unavailable due to obstruction warning
false alerts
radar sensor turns off and on
front collision radar sensor keeps going off and on.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Push Start and Ignition System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the push start and ignition system can leave the driver stranded or unable to start the vehicle.
symptoms: Push start button fails to operate
ignition switch fails to operate
push start feature fails to operate
brake pedal has to be pumped to release.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the electrical system can lead to unexpected behavior or failure of various vehicle systems, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Battery terminal connector corrosion
battery failure
push start has to be pressed multiple times
vehicle stalls or has difficulty starting.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the backup camera can increase the risk of accidents or injuries when reversing.
symptoms: Backup camera screen is black or shows static lines
backup camera fails to operate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the CVT transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, jerk, or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power
jerks
or stalls while driving
the transmission slips or hesitates
the RPMs rev up or down
the vehicle shakes or vibrates
and the transmission fails to engage or disengage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front axle can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: A popping noise is heard when backing out of the driveway
the front axle is worn out or failed
and the front crash light stays on constantly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The shuttering and slipping of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, jerk, or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission shuttering and slipping
the vehicle is difficult to control
the check engine light comes on
and the vehicle makes a loud squealing noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle activates the brakes on its own
the front radar obstruction warning is triggered
and the vehicle hesitates or lurches forward.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air cooling system can cause discomfort and distraction to the driver, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The air cooling system does not work
the air conditioning blows warm air
and the system leaks freon.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the back-up camera can cause accidents or injuries, especially when reversing.
symptoms: The back-up camera goes in and out
sometimes displaying a black screen
and only occurs when reversing.
